    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — discerning the author's intent in its original context, tracing the argument's logic, and hearing how this chapter speaks within the broader canonical conversation. 2 Samuel 23 operates simultaneously as a prophetic oracle, a Davidic testament, and a military honor roll. The movements below follow the chapter's own two-part structure: the theological word (vv. 1-7) and the military record (vv. 8-39), with particular attention to the episodes that carry theological weight.",
